@tkruse You're absolutely right, sir— the `buildSpec` check is more versatile: the only reason I didn't pick it up was that it allowed the `version` component to be empty, and I wasn't sure how the modified `GrabUtil` and `Grab` calls would deal with it.  I only left it out because of my own ignorance, there.  I'll definitely add the input tests from your branch here.

I saw the `reset()` method over in `PackageHandler`!  It'd be a heck of a lot nicer than having to toggle the event— but I couldn't get it to work out for re-loading completions.  What I thought\* have been happening was that the wrong instance of the class was getting the message— but I think\* that's wrong now.  I really think `reset()` is a better way to go.

I don't know how we're feeling, but Pull #104 might wind up being the way we want to go, anyhow; but I'll chug along and put some of the changes above in here.
